               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla samāʿtāta Ṗarāqliṭos “Vita of the Martyrs of Ṗarāqliṭos” (fols.
                     1ra-17rb), incomplete
 II) Taʾammǝra samāʿtāta Ṗarāqliṭos “Miracles of the
                     Martyrs of Ṗarāqliṭos”: 11 miracles (fols. 18ra-49vb) 
 - Introduction
                     (fols. 18ra-21rb)
 
 Additiones 1-2; colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="1ra" to="50rb"/>
                     <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5877DossierParaqlitos">Hagiographic Dossier of the Martyrs of
          Ṗarāqliṭos</title>
                     
                     <textLang xml:lang="gez"/>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                        <locus from="1ra" to="17rb"/>
                        <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1491Gadlas">Gadla Ṣādǝqān za-Ṗarāqliṭos</title>
                        <textLang xml:lang="gez"/>
                        <note>Text I is acephalous: the beginning is missing (which would correspond to the text on fols.
                           11ra-14va l.9 in Ms.<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESap046">AP-046</ref>).</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                        <locus from="18ra" to="49vb"/>
                        <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5878MiraclesParaqlitos"> Taʾammǝra samāʿtāta Ṗarāqliṭos: 11 miracles</title>
                        <textLang xml:lang="gez"/>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2.1">
                           <locus from="18ra" to="21rb"/>
                           <title>Introduction</title>
                        </msItem>
                        
                           
                           <note>- Text II contains the same miracles, with the same sequence, as in 
                              <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESap046">AP-046</ref>.</note>
                           <note>The miracles are 11. They are numbered, with the exception of miracles 5,
                              9 and 10. Miracle 11 is wrongly numbered as miracle 12; the same is in 
                              <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESap046">AP-046</ref>.</note>
                        
                     </msItem>
                     
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1" xml:lang="gez">
                        <locus from="49vb" to="50rb"/>:
                        ተፈጸመት፡ ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ በወርኃ፡ መጋቢት፡ እምስቡኡ፡ ሠርቀ፡
                        መዓልት፨ እም፳ወ፪ሠርቀ፡ ሌሊት፨ በ፸፻፡ በ፪፻፳ወ፱አመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ በመዋዕሊሁ፡ ለንጉሥነ፡
                        [<cb/>] ኢያሱ፨ ወልደ፡ በካፋ፡ እስመ፡ ቀሲስ፡ ዓምደ፡ ሚካኤል፡ በትግሐቱ፡ ዘአጸሐፋ፡ በጸሎተ፡ ...
                        [<cb/>] ለዘጸሐፋ፡ ወለዘጽሐፋ፡ ዓምደ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡
                        ወምስለ፡ ብእሲቱ፡ ወለተ፡ እስራኤል፡ ወምስለ፡ ደቂቁ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ጽጌ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ርእሰ፡ ሃይማኖት፨ ፨ 
                        <note>This
                        note states that the Ms. was completed in the month Maggābit of the Year of
                        Mercy 7229 (= <date when="1737">March/April 1737 A.D.</date>), during the time of King ʾIyasu II (r.
                        1730-1755). 
 Besides, it mentions the name of the commissioner, priest ʿAmda
                        Mikāʾel, who seems to be also the scribe (?), together with his wife Walatta
                        ʾƎsrāʾel and his children Takla Hāymānot, Ṣǝge Hāymānot and Rǝʾǝsä Hāymānot.</note>
                     </colophon>
                     
                     
                  </msItem>
                  
                  
